# GF(p) Field — abstract trait
#
# Per R-C's field design (see `.sstack/crypto-pure-simple-port/research/field_design.md`
# §2 "Unified Field API"), this declares the abstract surface that each concrete
# `Fe25519` / `FeP256` impl module satisfies.
#
# NOTE: Simple's `trait` does not yet support associated types (`type Repr`,
# `Self::Repr` were sketched in R-C §2 — they are aspirational, not language-supported
# today). For the I-4 scaffold we therefore expose the operations as free functions
# inside each impl module (`fe25519.spl`, `fe_p256.spl`) under a stable, documented
# naming convention. The trait below is a marker trait — it carries the contract in
# its docstring so callers can see, in one place, what every `Fe*` module guarantees.
#
# Once Simple gains trait associated types, this file can swap to the
# `trait Field: type Repr; fn fe_zero() -> Self::Repr; ...` shape without touching
# the impl modules.

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Field — abstract GF(p) interface contract
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

trait Field:
    """A finite field GF(p) of prime order.

    Every concrete impl module (`fe25519.spl`, `fe_p256.spl`, ...) must export
    free functions matching the contract below. The names are namespaced by
    module path (e.g. `std.common.math.field.fe25519.fe_add`).

    Contract (free-function form, per impl module):

        fn fe_zero() -> Self                     # additive identity
        fn fe_one()  -> Self                     # multiplicative identity
        fn fe_from_bytes(b: [u8]) -> Self        # 32-byte canonical decode
        fn fe_to_bytes(a: Self) -> [u8]          # 32-byte canonical encode (reduces first)
        fn fe_add(a: Self, b: Self) -> Self      # (a + b) mod p
        fn fe_sub(a: Self, b: Self) -> Self      # (a - b) mod p
        fn fe_neg(a: Self) -> Self               # (-a) mod p
        fn fe_mul(a: Self, b: Self) -> Self      # (a * b) mod p
        fn fe_sq(a: Self) -> Self                # (a * a) mod p
        fn fe_inv(a: Self) -> Self               # a^(p-2) mod p
        fn fe_pow(a: Self, e: [u8]) -> Self      # a^e mod p, exponent LE bytes, CT square-and-multiply-always
        fn fe_eq(a: Self, b: Self) -> bool       # constant-time, via XOR-accumulate + rt_black_box
        fn fe_is_zero(a: Self) -> bool           # constant-time, via reduce + OR + rt_black_box
        fn fe_cond_swap(a: Self, b: Self, swap: u64) -> (Self, Self)
                                                 # constant-time mask swap
        fn fe_cond_select(a: Self, b: Self, take_b: u64) -> Self
                                                 # constant-time selection; take_b in {0,1}

    CT-correctness: every op above is branch-free on its secret operands. Mask
    forms route the swap mask through `rt_black_box` (B6, commit d42cde3a0f) so
    that Cranelift cannot rebuild a data-dependent branch.

    Self-typed marker only: this trait body intentionally has no methods because
    Simple traits cannot yet bind a type variable to limb-tuple structs. Treat
    it as a documentation anchor.
    """
    nil
